      <section>
        <title>US'Veteran affairs loans</title>
        <chapter>
          <paragraph>Most popular loan type. Safe and affordable choice:100% financing Active and veteran military.
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <list type="unordered">
              <item>ACTIVE MILITARY: 74%</item>
              <item>VETERAN MILITARY: 54%</item>
            </list>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <list type="unordered">
              <item>ACTIVE: leading the majority financing , the entire home purchase</item>
              <item>VETERAN: putting down a median down payment of 5%</item>
              <item>CIVILIAN: putting down a median down payment of 11%</item>
            </list>
          </paragraph>
        </chapter>
        <chapter>
          <title>With the ability to obtain a VA Loan</title>
          <paragraph>buyers said saving for a down payment was the most difficult step:
            <list type="unordered">
              <item>ACTIVE: 3%</item>
              <item>VETERAN: 5%</item>
            </list>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>buyers said student loan debt delayed saving:
            <list type="unordered">
              <item>ACTIVE: 13%</item>
              <item>VETERAN: 4%</item>
            </list>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <list type="unordered">
              <item>ACTIVE: 43% have credit card debts</item>
              <item>VETERAN: 62% other debts</item>
            </list>
          </paragraph>
        </chapter>
